    <h2> Sydney Festival and Australia Day </h2>
    <p> Now that the entire December took place one event after another in Sydney, I assumed that it will be calmer again in January. Wrongly thought. One morning a colleague told me that the so -called Sydney Festival took place almost the entire January in Sydney. It is a cultural festival. So many concerts in the parks, exhibitions and even some sports ranking and the whole thing free of charge. </p>
    <p> I treated myself to the big opening concert in the park with a lot of jazz and gospel. </p>
