    <p> Since I would like to see much more of foreigners than what you can do in 4 weeks, I decided a long time ago that I will buy a little van. Either one that is already converted for backpackers or one that I convert myself. Look around the Internet and in a little bit <a title="&Ouml;ffnet im neuen Fenster" href="https://www.sydneytravellerscarmarket.com.au/" target="_blank"> Sydney Travelers Car Market </a> One day I stumbled over two really nice ladies from my hometown Rostock. Who absolutely had to get rid of their car named Hugo. </p>
    <p> Hugo is a red 1991 Mitsubishi Starwagon, which is converted and is equipped with all the necessary camping equipment. Unfortunately, Hugo was too expensive. I met the two girls two more times. At the last meeting they were really desperate to re -book their flights to New Zealand. </p>
